    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-04-13T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-04-13T22:00:00-05:00" n="387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3052: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-14T12:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 14, 1919, noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received April 15, 9.22
                        a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I had an informal conversation with the Minister for Foreign Affairs this
                    afternoon. I took occasion to refer to the Tientsin agitations [<hi
                        rend="italic">affair</hi>] in the tenor of your April 11th, 7 p.m. He
                    advised me that he has telegraphed to Obata<note n="30" xml:id="d387fn30"
                        >Torikichi Obata, Japanese Minister to China.</note> summary of facts, left
                    with Vice-Minister for Foreign Affairs last week and has instructed Obata to
                    make the necessary amends if it appeared from his investigation that any of the
                    Japanese involved were at fault.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
